===Etymology===
Named for [[w:Ruy López de Segura|Ruy López de Segura]], a Spanish priest who wrote a book about chess openings in 1561.

===Noun===
'''Ruy Lopez'''

# A common [[chess]] [[opening]], in which White moves king's bishop to the fifth rank.

